51.6	Pulitzer_Prize_for_Fiction	Pulitzer Prize for Fiction	The Pulitzer Prize for Fiction has been awarded for distinguished fiction by an American author, preferably dealing with American life. It originated as the Pulitzer Prize for the Novel, which was awarded between 1918 and 1947.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/22/Gen_pulitzer.jpg/200px-Gen_pulitzer.jpg
